    Scope and Contents
Bertot recalls his experiences as a coal miner in Coal City, Hillsboro and Auburn, Illinois. He recalls the daily activities of coal mining, company stores, wages, mules, types of coal, unions, accidents, safety precautions, and the modernization of coal mines. 2 tapes, 180 mins. 
Interview by Nick Cherniavsky, 1978 
